<c >Effects of the Virus on Wookiee Biology:</c>

<c >After initial exposure to the virus, the effects remain consistent with that of any other species. Apparent loss of sanity over only a few minutes. However, there are a few differences that should be noted. The test subject in question began screaming about wookiee younglings and how mounds of its clan and children were burning, rotting, and melting even. Shortly after, the more physical irregularities could be noticed.

The wookiee's throat began to inflate, much like a balloon, as it started choking and gagging, suffocating from whatever fluid was likely building up. It eventually grew so much that it even popped like such a balloon, leading the wookiee to expire within only a few seconds from blood loss. If it hadn't happened, though, it's likely it wouldn't have been long before the suffocation would have done so.

Prior to the reanimation process that was evident in all other subjects, closer inspection revealed an acute swelling of the tongue, as well, blocking off any and all air through the throat. Bit harsh if you ask me. Suffocation, either way.

Following reanimation, it shows aggression consistent with the other subjects, though perhaps a bit more-so due to the difference in strength with a wookiee.

Tests will continue. End of log.</c>

The terminal appears to contain a database of experiment logs pertaining to this cell.

----

<c >Effects of the Virus on Whiphid Biology:</c>

<c >While it was rather difficult to perform a direct injection on such a creature, we did eventually manage. Within minutes, it began to show similar symptoms of insanity, consistent with every other test subjects. But the physical abnormalities separate it from the others.

While necrosis isn't unusual in these tests, shortly after initial injection, the site began to suffer from heavy swelling and rapid necrosis. Following this, it seemed to rapidly develop sores all over its body that quickly popped open and began spewing out think discharges of blood and puss. It was also noted that the tusks on the whiphid's lower jaw quickly changed colour to that of a sickly yellow shade.

Even prior to death, the insanity almost seemed to give it a boost in strength, which ultimate led to the deaths of two personnel in the containment unit. Aside from that, however, the death and reanimation seems consistent with other subjects.

Tests will continue. End log.</c>
A good sauce pan is every cook's friend.  Both for boiling potatoes, and restoring order. Grab this pan, open one can of whoop-ass, and do lunch!

Value.value: Upon exiting the turbolift, you get an immediate sense of unease, far greater than the lower level. As if the very air around you is telling you to turn back. The darkness of this level almost seems to close in on you, like some oppressive force. The screams of those things echo through the halls from time to time, mixed in with the faint echoing banging of something further in.

This room appears pretty barren, save for the giant conference table right in the center. The flickering remains of a hologram hovers above it, though it's impossible to tell what it was once meant to be. Much like has become the norm in this station, the smell of copper and rot hits you fairly hard, here. Be on your guard.

Entering this lab cell, you are assailed again by a powerful smell of copper and rot. Looking around, it's very dark in here but looking around, it looks like some sort of containment and testing lab.

Entering this lab cell, you are assailed again by a powerful smell of copper and rot. Looking around, it's very dark in here but looking around, it looks like some sort of containment and testing lab.

Upon entering this cell, you can make out a few bits of tech faintly glowing around the room. The odd hologram displays flickering on and off in some places. However, it's hard to make out much in the room. Just before you is a giant centrifuge of sort, holding large containment cylinders of some sort, surrounding by what are likely observation terminals.

Behind the centrifuge from where you entered, you come across three distinct glass containers. They are unlit, but upon closer inspection, you see the humanoid shapes within them. They are hooked up to tubes, entering and exiting their bodies in places. They seem perfectly motionless, however. But you can't help but notice the obvious thing, that the right-most container has been broken open and whatever was inside is missing...

Approaching the right side of the room, you notice a couple containment units off to the left, but the thing that seems to catch your eye are the three containment tubes ahead, next to the wall. As you approach, the contents of the clear tubes becomes apparent: Pairs of human lungs floating in the suspension fluid. Connected to them are large metal tubes feeding in and out of them, before reaching a large metal containment unit to the right of them. The one thing that seems to catch you off-guard, however, is the sound made from the lungs. As if taking momentary breath, they let out an eerie scream.

The room here appears a bit different, as if more of a dedicated observation unit of sorts. Through the darkness you can make out the blinking of all sorts of terminals dotted around. But the one thing that stands out is the large glass containment tube in the center of the room... and it's broken open and empty.

Entering through the doors, this room appears about as dark as the rest, save for the faint blinking of lights come from rows of panels to the right. Upon closer inspection, this appears like some sort of server or reference room for the researchers here. Just like that, you hear a faint click to your right as one of the terminals still carries enough power to show a readout.
The banging you heard upon arrival seems to be even louder now, coming from somewhere beyond the door ahead.

Moving through the door, you enter into some sort of checkpoint. The banging sound is almost deafening now, accompanied by a distinct gurgling growl, muffled by the massive bulkhead doors ahead of you. To the left and right are likely containment procedures in the event of whatever's inside escaping. Large, manned cannons can be seen on either side, though the left has forcefields still active, while the right seems to have malfunctioned. Whatever is beyond those doors, however, sounds very dangerous... and very hungry.

After finally making your ways through the bulkhead door, you had noticed the banging stopped. It's then that you hear the heavy sounds of something very big moving towards you, gurgling growls echoing through the darkness. A massive, half-rotting rancor lumbers towards you, hungry for another meal.
Curiously, on the far end of the rancor's containment unit, there's a turbolift. Where could it lead?
